Social interactions tracking: Track how different people make you feel and get an eagles eye view of your relationships. New UI: We have improved the Settings component and updated it so you can easily customize the app. Bug fixes and performance improvements.

Medication tracking: If you wish to track medications you can now do so. You will be able to see how different dosages affect your mood. Physical activity tracking: When it comes to mental health physical activity can have the greatest impact. Track how physical activity makes you feel.

Bug fixes
Moodflow 4.0 brings a completely new UI and a ton of bug fixes.

Moodflow Plus: The Plus version adds extra features to the already existing ones. For example backing up images within entries to the cloud. Images: A picture is worth a thousand words. Add an image to your entry! More activities icons: Added more than 50 new icons to choose from!
Search! Now you are able to search for anything anytime! Sunday week start: Now you can enable the week to start on Sunday. Performance! Small but needed performance improvement.

Multiple Notifications!: If it s hard for you to enter multiple entries a day now you can get multiple reminders a day. Custom Rating Describers: Now you can describe days in a way that suits you better. Rebranding!: Mood Pixel is now called Moodflow. Hope you guys like the new name and logo! Bug fixes and improvements.

Multiple Entries: Log all the moods you want and see how your mood evolves throughout the day. Dot Style: Instead of the whole day block taking up the color now you can display a small dot with the days color. Side Menu: You can now access Settings by tapping the top left of the screen. Also quotes have been added.
Custom Background: Use your own images as a background. Bug fixes and improvements.

Geolocation: Add your current location to your entries. A map feature will be added in the future. Disable Gradients: You are now able to disable gradients if you favor flat look. Activities Statistics: See how many activities you did in a month. Filtering by activities is coming soon. Sorted Emotions: Emotions are now sorted alphabetically to make it easier to find a mood. Bug fixes and improvements.

Past: Now you are able to access your past years! A feature that was necessary sooner or later. Performance: Hope you can notice the small performance improvement that is coming with this release. Statistics: Press the name of a month with entries to see statistics about that month. New Moods Layout: Now you can see your custom moods in a new way: SEGMENT 2 New Menu Button: In settings under Layout you can enable or disable the floating menu button. Multiple Challenges: Now you can have multiple challenges. Sorry for the inconvenience. Bug Fixes: Repaired issues here and there... again. Specially the notifications bug.
Activities: Track activities the easiest way possible! Pinlock: Have privacy with your own 4 digit PIN. Bug fixes and improvements.
New features!!! Bug fixes and improvements.

Google Drive Backup: Save your data to your Google Drive account seamlessly. Habits Challenges: Accomplish 28 day challenges and form new and better habits. Better Statistics: See your mood evolve in the new chart within the statistics panel. Bug fixes and improvements.
Background Manager: Customize the background the way you like it. Inspiration Mode: Enter Zen mode and write everything with no obstructions. Bug fixes and improvements.

Color Editor: Create your own mood color palettes and customize the app the way you like it!. Improved Journal Mode Layout: Read your entries in a more immersive way. The limit on characters for each entry has been lifted. Languages: Use Mood Pixel in the following languages: Spanish English French or Portuguese. Bug fixes and improvements.

Mood Manager: Edit and customize the default moods as well as the layout. Plus 60 new emotions for you to better describe your moods. Layout Customization: Decide whether to show certain months or not. Decide if you want to highlight the current day! Bug fixes and improvements.

Journal mode: Read all your entries at once with the new journal mode. Select from different color palettes and enjoy a more custom experience. Fixed muting audio of other apps when launching Mood Pixel. Support for a better layout for phones with a notch.
